      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLACK STAR RIOT (5) jumped from box 8 last time and ran away with an impressive win scoring by 9 lengths at Warrnambool in a handy 24.91. Has the squeeze box to overcome and will need the breaks early. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Well placed and will be tough to beat. TRIPPED OUT (1) goes very well this course and distance starting seven times for three wins and three minors. Hit the frame latest (30.37) when second at this track in a Grade 5. Looks one of the chances. FLYING DUCATI (8) has a strong record here with two wins and a minor from five starts. Hit the frame latest (25.61) when third at Shepparton in a Grade 5 FIN. Looks suited here and can measure up. PRESIDENT ROLEX (3) is building a sequence of top-three results and can add to the tally.",
